with liquid courage?

108
00:05:35,181 --> 00:05:37,984
Or drunken...?

109
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:50,530
Where do your parents live?

110
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,201
What do you want to do?

111
00:05:55,935 --> 00:05:57,637
To meet my parents?

112
00:06:01,474 --> 00:06:02,008
No.

113
00:06:02,008 --> 00:06:04,244
I've just been really thinking lately,

114
00:06:04,244 --> 00:06:07,480
what if they

115
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,482
disagree?

116
00:06:12,152 --> 00:06:13,520
I think it's better for you

117
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:15,155
to feel them out first.

118
00:06:15,155 --> 00:06:16,389
After all, they're the elders.

119
00:06:18,558 --> 00:06:21,361
Don't make a family revolution

120
00:06:21,361 --> 00:06:23,730
and get kicked out of the clinic.

121
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:30,503
What if I do it

122
00:06:30,503 --> 00:06:33,139
and am left with nothing?

123
00:06:33,139 --> 00:06:35,809
Will you still be by my side?

124
00:06:43,349 --> 00:06:45,185
I won't.

125
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:50,290
What did you say?

126
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:52,759
I won't leave you.

127
00:06:55,128 --> 00:06:56,696
My sister used to say

128
00:06:56,696 --> 00:07:00,533
it would be hard
for people to be with me.

129
00:07:02,168 --> 00:07:03,369
Why?

130
00:07:04,404 --> 00:07:06,239
Because I'm difficult.

131
00:07:07,307 --> 00:07:09,008
Are you?

132
00:07:09,008 --> 00:07:11,211
Always pretending to be cool.

133
00:07:11,211 --> 00:07:12,679
I don't think so.

134
00:07:13,613 --> 00:07:15,949
And like posturing.

135
00:07:15,949 --> 00:07:17,717
A little bit.

136
00:07:17,717 --> 00:07:19,152
Hey!

137
00:07:21,187 --> 00:07:22,889
And she said

138
00:07:22,889 --> 00:07:24,924
when I was young,
I liked to pretend to be an adult,

139
00:07:24,924 --> 00:07:27,127
so I lacked innocence,

140
00:07:27,127 --> 00:07:31,064
and I may become more naive
as I grow older.

141
00:07:31,064 --> 00:07:35,235
It's okay. You have me.

142
00:07:37,937 --> 00:07:39,405
Xun'an.

143
00:07:39,405 --> 00:07:44,210
We need to learn
how to reassure each other

144
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:46,880
and stay together.

145
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,348
We can quarrel

146
00:07:48,348 --> 00:07:51,017
but we must solve it together.

147
00:07:51,017 --> 00:07:55,054
If one of us doesn't communicate,

148
00:07:55,054 --> 00:07:58,958
the other will be patient and wait,

149
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,260
okay?

150
00:08:01,461 --> 00:08:03,963
You should say it to yourself.

151
00:08:03,963 --> 00:08:07,433
I'm always patient with you.

152
00:08:07,433 --> 00:08:09,769
♪I don't want you to be♪

153
00:08:09,769 --> 00:08:12,639
Then you give me more confidence.

154
00:08:13,435 --> 00:08:16,937
♪And forgotten♪

155
00:08:18,344 --> 00:08:22,081
You are handcuffed and you can't escape.

156
00:08:23,716 --> 00:08:25,485
Xun'an.

157
00:08:28,621 --> 00:08:31,791
Je t'aime. A.
[*I love you, A]

158
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:33,560
These French words are so romantic.

159
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:37,163
But what does this "A" mean?

160
00:08:38,865 --> 00:08:40,466
I don't know.

161
00:08:40,466 --> 00:08:42,202
Ask yourself.

162
00:08:42,202 --> 00:08:44,103
Tell me.

163
00:08:44,103 --> 00:08:47,104
♪I don't want you to be♪

164
00:08:47,841 --> 00:08:49,209
What about yours?

165
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:53,146
Here.

166
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:57,183
♪I should believe this♪

167
00:08:57,183 --> 00:08:59,853
But I didn't carve anything on it.

168
00:08:59,853 --> 00:09:02,322
Leave it to you.

169
00:09:04,157 --> 00:09:05,658
Leave it to me.

170
00:09:05,888 --> 00:09:09,527
♪And forgotten♪

171
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:21,056
(White Dark Bistro & Flavor)

172
00:09:50,503 --> 00:09:52,438
(Pink Lady.)

173
00:09:52,438 --> 00:09:54,707
(I'm into you.)

174
00:10:18,197 --> 00:10:19,966
Mr. Jin Xun'an.

175
00:10:19,966 --> 00:10:22,402
You have the right to remain silent.

176
00:10:22,402 --> 00:10:25,038
Any statement can be used

177
00:10:25,038 --> 00:10:27,740
against you in judicial proceedings.

178
00:10:29,409 --> 00:10:31,678
Some people say

179
00:10:31,678 --> 00:10:35,248
eyes and hearts are connected.

180
00:10:35,248 --> 00:10:38,217
It was these eyes

181
00:10:38,217 --> 00:10:41,587
that made me not afraid.

182
00:10:41,587 --> 00:10:46,559
Slowly, my love for them

183
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:49,796
spread to my heart.

184
00:10:52,231 --> 00:10:54,867
Do you agree with the above?

185
00:10:57,837 --> 00:11:00,573
I'll take your look as a yes.

186
00:11:00,573 --> 00:11:03,343
Hand out. Hurry up.

187
00:11:03,343 --> 00:11:05,345
Left hand.

188
00:11:08,748 --> 00:11:10,316
Be gentle.

189
00:11:10,316 --> 00:11:11,751
Don't move.

190
00:11:14,087 --> 00:11:15,288
Stay still.

191
00:11:21,294 --> 00:11:24,998
From now on, you will be my man.

192
00:11:24,998 --> 00:11:26,699
No resistance.

193
00:11:26,699 --> 00:11:28,534
No complaint.

194
00:11:28,534 --> 00:11:30,370
Did you hear me?

195
00:11:36,309 --> 00:11:37,810
The play is over?

196
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:41,481
Childish. Go cook quickly.

197
00:11:41,481 --> 00:11:43,483
(My love, my heart.)
What? Childish?

198
00:11:43,483 --> 00:11:45,885
(My love, my heart.)
This is romance, okay?

199
00:11:47,453 --> 00:11:49,689
